article.headline: Eastern Illinois 65, Western Illinois 62
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. (AP) -- Emanuel Dildy scored 19 points, including a 3-point shot with six seconds left, to boost Eastern Illinois to a 65-62 win over Western Illinois on Tuesday. The Panthers (5-4) had a 62-49 lead with 5:40 left but the Leathernecks went on a 13 point run to tie the score at 62 with 38 seconds left before Dildy's basket. Josh Gomes also had 17 points for Eastern Illinois, which outrebounded Western Illinois 38-27 and shot 20 of 41 from the field. Troy Okeson finished with 18 points for Western Illinois (4-6). Eulis Baez and Will Lewis each added 16 points. The Leathernecks shot just 23 of 58 from the field and were 5 of 19 from 3-point range.
